<html><p>Adobe will stop distributing and updating its&nbsp;<a href="https://www.adobe.com/products/flashplayer/enterprise-end-of-life.html">Flash Player after 31 December 2020</a>, with the major browser vendors removing Adobe Flash support at the same time. Adobe Flash components in software products will no longer function after this date.</p>

<p>Server Automation versions 2018.08, 10.60, 10.51 and 10.23 included a few Flash-based components. There are patches for each of these versions to remove the Adobe Flash-based components.&nbsp;The patches are available on&nbsp;<a href="https://softwaresupport.softwaregrp.com/document?doctype=patches">https://softwaresupport.softwaregrp.com/document?doctype=patches</a>.&nbsp;Here are the direct links for your convenience:&nbsp;</p>

<ul>
	<li>SA 2018.08.008:&nbsp;<a href="https://softwaresupport.softwaregrp.com/doc/KM03660756">https://softwaresupport.softwaregrp.com/doc/KM03660756</a></li>
	<li>SA 10.60.018:&nbsp;<a href="https://softwaresupport.softwaregrp.com/doc/KM03673896">https://softwaresupport.softwaregrp.com/doc/KM03673896</a></li>
	<li>SA 10.51.014:&nbsp;<a href="https://softwaresupport.softwaregrp.com/doc/KM03672732">https://softwaresupport.softwaregrp.com/doc/KM03672732</a></li>
	<li>SA 10.23.018:&nbsp;<a href="https://softwaresupport.softwaregrp.com/doc/KM03670731">https://softwaresupport.softwaregrp.com/doc/KM03670731</a></li>
</ul>

<p>SA functionality that contained Adobe Flash</p>

<ul>
	<li>Real Time Graph –&nbsp;An alternative has been available since SA 10.50 in the standard SA desktop client. For versions of SA older than SA 10.50, consider invoking the Run OS Build Plan Program APX (Program Extension). Alternatively, you can use the API to provision using the OSBP feature</li>
	<li>iLO Integration - An alternative will be available in the standard SA desktop client. Alternatively, you can invoke the API to use the feature</li>
	<li>Add Static Information for Servers -&nbsp;&nbsp;Use the Custom Attribute interface to manage the static information for servers</li>
	<li>HP-UX Provisioning -&nbsp;The HP-UX provisioning feature will be removed from the product</li>
</ul>

<p>In addition to removing Adobe Flash, upgrading to 2018.08 or DCA&nbsp;offers additional benefits that help you automate your datacenter.</p>

